What you need to know:

Jackson Masesi, who runs Bee-Care Apiaries Limited makes three varieties of peanut products; one blended with honey, another pure while the third one crunchy.The whole process starts with separating quality peanuts from impurities such as leaves, pieces of shells and rotten nuts.To avoid aflatoxin, Karuiru advises farmers to ensure the nuts have minimal exposure to moisture by drying them well under the sun after harvesting.MARKUP project national coordinator Maina Karuiru says farmers need to know the benefits of quality production, for better produce and higher earning.